reviews.review_text: little nugget within The jam out of Truckin' into the WRS Prelude is really special with some slide work.

4 stars on setlist alone. The show will download in order.  However, the first two songs of the night are mis-titled.  BIODTL and BE Women are actually Promised Land and 1/2 Step and are in the proper order.  Just misnamed.  Will review at length latter.  The sound is good too, though, from the 6 first set songs I've heard.  Doubt this will go down to 3 stars.

Great Show The sound quality of this show is great.  It should be downloaded for the DEW alone.  Another legendary 73 show.  I feel like a broken record saying legendary 73 show.  But then again, weren't they all?????

1973!!! Great sound, the boys rocked B-more again 6 months after the legendary 9-17-72 show. The Playin on this one is a highlight for the month.
Wolfman Jack comes out and introduces them before the second set, and they go right into Ramble On Rose...
awesome!
tone and stuff Did anyone really listen to the fantastic tone on Jerry's guitar on Candyman, especially in the solo......holy crap it's all vibrato slow and steady......man!

Candyman Your right Jerry sounds great in the mix...a little off vocally but easily forgiven.
Good stuff....

Re: I thought this show was overrated when I first heard it.  I was wrong, the jam into Wharf Rat (after the WRS section) is a thing of beauty, a touch of exotica that recalls perhaps the 9/21/72 "Star," which had Middle Eastern overtones.

CandyMan o Man Wow, I love 73, this band was put togther right all year, and this show is a reminder of it. 


magic here is found after wrs, after the first 2 minutes of the music-less lyrics rendition, jerry keith phil and an uptempo billy space it out for 6 more minutes. this is a one of a kind moment that steals the cake at least for the month of march, enroute to probubly the best rat i've heard. The madness bubbles over at about the 3:37 mark.  

73 is full of these little moments that if you search you will find a chest full of treasures. check out the pitb from the 28th, the jam into stand alone rider from the 31st, the runaway sunshine from april 2nd, quite a week. 

email me at fieldhouse11277@hotmail.com happy to share/trade

Might be a 5,but it keeps skipping songs:( I don't know if they've reconfigured the archive or what, but I can't even stream a whole show.  I'm getting every other song, which turns into a real drag when you get to the jam and it cuts ahead to the next tune, or like Weather Report Suite you just get the intro and then it cuts ahead. I'm no tech head, so maybe I'm hittin the wrong button on the stream, but somethin tells me somethin is up.

Not bad The recording quality is better than average.  4 of 5.  What is annoying is all the tuning in between songs is found at the beginning of a song, not the end of the previous one.  So when you listen to, say  Jack Straw, you have to wait 45 seconds through the tuning to hear the song.

The tuning should have been cut to be on the end of the previous song.

On second thought, not worth the download.  The tuning is at the beginning of each song, and that is incredibly annoying.
Are You Serious you would keep from downloading this special nook of history over some tuning? Ill download it twice then...Just for you!
Wolfman Jack Light up if you Love The Dead

rockin baltimore this is one of my favorite 73 show's the sound is out of this world the whole show rocks!!!!! nothing left to say but enjoy!!!!!peace wwd!!                :)

Reach out and Grab Ya.. I don't know why but this page has a depth of sound that seems to be missing from the other copy of this concert..and its a terrific one! I thought I might have been there(guess it was the other Civic Center show)but this one is better..great list of songs.Is that Donna? Shes' right on the harmonies, and Jerry Garcias' vocals are deep and clear. Wharf Rat, Candyman,just incredible..

Just like Wolfman Jack! I love Wolfman Jack coming out and talking right before Ramblin Rose. Nice touch, as always boys.

thanks archive.org!!
playing in the band great sound.a hot playing in the band and very nice morning dew.
